<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>glXDestroyGLXPixmap</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets Vsnapshot" /></head><body><div class="refentry"><a id="glXDestroyGLXPixmap"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glXDestroyGLXPixmap — destroy a GLX pixmap</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><table border="0" class="funcprototype-table" summary="Function synopsis" style="cellspacing: 0; cellpadding: 0;"><tr><td><code class="funcdef">void <strong class="fsfunc">glXDestroyGLXPixmap</strong>(</code></td><td>Display * <var class="pdparam">dpy</var>, </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td>GLXPixmap <var class="pdparam">pix</var><code>)</code>;</td></tr></table><div class="funcprototype-spacer"> </div></div></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="parameters"></a><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl class="variablelist"><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>dpy</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the connection to the X server.
                </p></dd><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>pix</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies the GLX pixmap to be destroyed.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="description"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            If the GLX pixmap <em class="parameter"><code>pix</code></em> is not current to any client,
            <code class="function">glXDestroyGLXPixmap</code> destroys it immediately.
            Otherwise,
            <em class="parameter"><code>pix</code></em> is destroyed when it becomes not current to any client.
            In either case, the resource ID
            is freed immediately.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="errors"></a><h2>Errors</h2><p>
            <code class="constant">GLXBadPixmap</code> is generated if <em class="parameter"><code>pix</code></em> is not a valid GLX pixmap.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="seealso"></a><h2>See Also</h2><p>
